    <div class="callout info">
      <div class="callout-title">📚 Chapter Overview</div>
      <p>RAG systems enhance LLMs by retrieving relevant information from knowledge bases before generating responses. This chapter covers RAG architecture, implementation patterns, and best practices.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="callout info">
      <div class="callout-title">📌 Learning objectives</div>
      <ul>
        <li>Explain why retrieval helps with grounding, freshness, and transparency</li>
        <li>Identify the core RAG pipeline stages (ingest → embed → index → retrieve → generate)</li>
        <li>Choose chunking strategies and explain trade-offs (precision vs. context)</li>
        <li>Compare dense, sparse, and hybrid retrieval and when to use each</li>
